answer:
In 2010, 2 human papillomavirus (HPV) vaccines were approved in Canada: CERVARIX® (approved February 2010) and GARDASIL® (approved July 2006). Genital warts (condyloma acuminata) are caused by HPV subtypes 6 and 11, which cause 90% of genital warts. Only the GARDASIL® vaccine provides protection against those subtypes. To know which vaccine you received, check your immunization records. Our tips for finding your records are here.
Immunization Nurse
